Attributes.description: Classical and contemporary metaphors for memory and their impact on theory development.
Attributes.prereq: Pre-reqs: Either (a) PSYC 100 or (b) two of PSYC 101, PSYC 102, PSYC 205, PSYC 207, PSYC 208, PSYC 216, PSYC 217, PSYC 277. (Strongly recommended: PSYC 101 and either PSYC 216 or one of PSYC 217 or 277. Non-PSYC students may substitute LING 420 or LING 200 and 201 for the above prerequisite.)
